{% extends "core/emails/base.html.j2" %}
{% block title %}Time to Upload Your First SBOM - sbomify{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
    <h1>Time to upload your first SBOM, {{ user.first_name|default:user.username }}!</h1>
    <p>
        Great job creating your first component! Now let's upload an SBOM to see what's inside
        your software and find any security issues.
    </p>
    <h2>What Is an SBOM?</h2>
    <div class="highlight-box">
        <p>
            A Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) is like an ingredient list for your software.
            It shows all the libraries and dependencies that make up your app, helping you
            find known security vulnerabilities.
        </p>
    </div>
    <h2>Upload Options</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>
            <strong>GitHub Action (Recommended):</strong> Automatically generate and upload SBOMs
            with every push using our
            <a href="https://github.com/sbomify/sbomify-action" target="_blank">official GitHub Action</a>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Manual upload:</strong> Already have an SBOM? Upload it directly â€” we support
            both SPDX and CycloneDX formats
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h2>What Happens After Upload?</h2>
    <p>Once you upload your SBOM, sbomify will automatically:</p>
    <ul class="feature-list">
        <li>Validate your SBOM file</li>
        <li>Catalog all dependencies</li>
        <li>Scan for known vulnerabilities</li>
        <li>Generate compliance reports</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin: 32px 0;">
        <a href="{{ app_base_url }}/components/" class="button">Upload Your First SBOM</a>
    </p>
{% endblock %}
